lines.text: Analytic Insight, Inc.
—Genesis: Dippers' Discussion Guide—
I.
Warm-Up
(Explain procedures, mirror, tape, etc. Explain that moderator is an
independent researcher who is interested in making sure that everyone has
a chance to share their opinion. Please be frank.)
Introductions: [Ask each respondent to introduce himself.] What is your
current brand? What do you like about that brand?
Are there any other brands that you've tried recently? Why did you try that
one? (Probe especially for any concerns about excess juice, tobacco
particles in teeth, or other social concerns.)
What other brands have you dipped? Why did you switch to the one you're
dipping now?
Cigarettes and Other Smoking: Do you ever smoke cigarettes, pipes, or
cigars? (If so, ask:) What's good about smoking? What are problems
connected with smoking? (Encourage a general discussion of the
pleasures and perceived drawbacks of smoking.)
Other Smokeless Tobacco Alternatives: Have you ever tried any other
forms of smokeless tobacco? (lf so:) What did you think of that? Why
did you try it? (Encourage discussion of reasons for trying other
smokeless tobacco products.)
What did you like about that product? Dislike? (Encourage a brief
discussion, as appropriate, of the advantages and disadvantages of
other forms of smokeless tobacco.)
Do ever wish there were some other way of enjoying tobacco taste and
satisfaction? Why do you say that?' (Probe only insofar as
respondents spontaneously develop ideas at this point.)
